---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Base
  title="Meet Paul Gibbons | AI Strategist, Author and Keynote Speaker"
  description="Paul Gibbons: 30 years helping leaders get the human side of technology right. Author of 8 books, AI adoption strategist, and keynote speaker."
>
  <Nav />

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 1: HERO
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bio-hero">
    <div class="bio-hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="bio-hero-content">
      <div class="bio-hero-text">
        <div class="section-label">Meet Paul</div>
        <h1 class="bio-hero-headline">30 Years Helping Leaders Get the Human Side of Technology Right</h1>
        <blockquote class="bio-hero-quote">
          "Attempting to build 21st-century 'intelligent enterprises' with analog 20th-century ideas on leadership and change is a recipe for failure."
          <cite>Paul Gibbons, The Science of Organizational Change</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <div class="bio-hero-image">
        <img
          src="/images/paul-speaking.jpg"
          alt="Paul Gibbons - polymath, polyglot, full-stack AI advisory"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 2: BIOGRAPHY
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bio-main" id="biography">
    <div class="bio-main-inner">

      <div class="bio-kpmg-quote reveal">
        <p>Simon Collins, Chairman, KPMG: "Paul never told us what we wanted to hear; he told us what we needed to hear."</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bio-block reveal">
        <div class="section-label">Intelligence and Enterprises</div>
        <h2 class="bio-headline accent-green">Navigating the Great Collisions</h2>
        <div class="bio-body">
          <p>Ranked "top-50 to follow in AI" on LinkedIn in 2025, Paul works at the intersection of human behavior and technological acceleration. His 9th book, <em>Adopting AI, The People-first Approach</em>, was rated "best book on AI in 2025" in one review.</p>
          <p>He helps boards and C-suite leaders build the cognitive infrastructure needed for the next decade, specializing in separating strategic signal from the "sludge and slop" of management hype — delivering digital transformations and AI adoption that are rooted in evidence, ethics, and rigorous behavioral science.</p>
          <p>For clients, this means moving beyond "silver bullet" solutions to create resilient cultures that can thrive during the overlapping revolutions in intelligence, markets, and work.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bio-block reveal">
        <h2 class="bio-headline accent-blue">Think Bigger, Think Better</h2>
        <div class="bio-body">
          <p>Paul is the mind behind <em>Think Bigger Think Better</em>, a long-form project — books, Substack, and podcast — dedicated to helping citizens and leaders make sense of a world where AI is rewriting power and truth. His work is defined by a unique dual lens: debunking tech nonsense while importing high-level ideas from philosophy, economics, and neuroscience into the real-world machinery of global organizations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bio-block reveal">
        <h2 class="bio-headline accent-purple">A Legacy of Bringing Science to Leadership and Change</h2>
        <div class="bio-body">
          <p>For over three decades, Paul has advised the world's leading firms — including PwC, IBM, HSBC, Deloitte, and KPMG — on their most complex human challenges: ethics, cultural disruption, and large-scale innovation.</p>
          <p>His global reputation is anchored by eight books, including the seminal <em>The Science of Organizational Change</em>, ranked among the top change management texts of all time, and the first book to bring behavioral science to leadership and change. <em>Change Myths</em> pioneered the use of critical thinking tools for human capital professionals. <em>The Future of Change Management</em> showed how "change has to change."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bio-block reveal">
        <h2 class="bio-headline accent-orange">The 2026 Horizon</h2>
        <div class="bio-body">
          <p>Paul's current research focuses on AI literacy and "2026: The Year of Multiple Revolutions." He maps the simultaneous shifts in health, intelligence, and truth, helping organizations prepare for a future where "human-first" isn't just a slogan, but a competitive necessity.</p>
          <p>His clients and audiences include Google, Microsoft, HSBC, and the London School of Economics.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bio-block reveal">
        <h2 class="bio-headline">Background and Expertise</h2>
        <div class="bio-body">
          <p>With a career spanning quantitative finance, consulting, and academia, Paul's multidisciplinary outlook is informed by studies in molecular biology, economics, and philosophy. A European by upbringing now living in Colorado, Paul competes internationally in poker and mind sports — a testament to his lifelong obsession with how humans can think better in an age of accelerating change.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       POLYMATH INFOGRAPHIC
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bio-polymath">
    <div class="bio-polymath-inner reveal">
      <img
        src="/images/polymath_business_image.avif"
        alt="The Polymath of Modern Business — Expert on the human side of technology, global finance to tier-1 consulting, foundation in science philosophy and human behaviour, tests ideas in high-stakes mindsports, author of eight books on business and leadership, ranked number 3 globally for corporate culture"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 3: CLIENT STRIP
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bio-clients" id="clients">
    <div class="bio-clients-inner reveal">
      <div class="section-label" style="text-align:center;">Trusted by leaders worldwide</div>
      <p class="bio-clients-list">Amex, Barclays, Comcast, HSBC, Morgan Stanley, BP, the NHS, the FT, Bloomberg, KPMG, Deloitte, IBM, Shell, Google, Microsoft, PwC</p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
       SECTION 4: TESTIMONIALS
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bio-testimonials" id="testimonials">
    <div class="bio-testimonials-inner">
      <div class="section-label" style="text-align:center;">What Leaders Say</div>
      <div class="bio-testimonials-track">
        <div class="bio-testimonial-card">
          <p class="bio-testimonial-text">"Paul never told us what we wanted to hear, he told us what we needed to hear."</p>
          <p class="bio-testimonial-author">Simon Collins, Chairman KPMG</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <Footer />
</Base>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     SCOPED STYLES
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<style>
  /* ── HERO ── */
  .bio-hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 120px 48px 0;
  }

  .bio-hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 70% 40%, rgba(60, 40, 20, 0.7), transparent),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 50% at 20% 80%, rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.05), transparent),
      linear-gradient(170deg, var(--espresso) 0%, var(--chocolate) 40%, var(--chocolate-mid) 100%);
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .bio-hero-content {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 100%;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .bio-hero-text {
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .bio-hero-headline {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 56px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(30px);
    animation: fadeInUp 0.8s ease forwards 0.4s;
  }

  .bio-hero-quote {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.6vw, 18px);
    color: var(--gold);
    line-height: 1.6;
    border: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(20px);
    animation: fadeInUp 0.8s ease forwards 0.7s;
  }

  .bio-hero-quote cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: rgba(245, 240, 232, 0.4);
  }

  .bio-hero-image {
    position: relative;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(40px);
    animation: fadeInRight 1s ease forwards 0.5s;
    align-self: stretch;
    min-height: 500px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .bio-hero-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
    filter: brightness(0.9) contrast(1.05);
  }

  .bio-hero-image::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 120px;
    background: linear-gradient(transparent, var(--espresso));
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .bio-hero { padding: 120px 24px 0; }
    .bio-hero-content { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
    .bio-hero-image { max-width: 500px; min-height: 400px; }
  }


  /* ── BIOGRAPHY ── */
  .bio-main {
    padding: 100px 48px;
    background: var(--chocolate-mid);
  }

  .bio-main-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .bio-kpmg-quote {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    padding-bottom: 60px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.15);
  }

  .bio-kpmg-quote p {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 24px);
    color: rgba(245, 240, 232, 0.65);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .bio-block {
    margin-bottom: 72px;
  }

  .bio-block:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio-headline {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 40px);
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .bio-headline.accent-green { color: var(--accent-green); }
  .bio-headline.accent-blue { color: var(--accent-blue); }
  .bio-headline.accent-purple { color: var(--accent-purple); }
  .bio-headline.accent-orange { color: var(--accent-orange); }

  .bio-body p {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: rgba(245, 240, 232, 0.75);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .bio-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio-body em {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .bio-body strong {
    color: var(--cream);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .bio-main { padding: 80px 24px; }
  }


  /* ── POLYMATH INFOGRAPHIC ── */
  .bio-polymath {
    padding: 80px 48px;
    background: var(--espresso);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.08);
  }

  .bio-polymath-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .bio-polymath-inner img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.12);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .bio-polymath { padding: 60px 24px; }
  }


  /* ── CLIENT STRIP ── */
  .bio-clients {
    padding: 80px 48px;
    background: var(--espresso);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.08);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.08);
  }

  .bio-clients-inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .bio-clients-list {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 2;
    color: rgba(245, 240, 232, 0.5);
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .bio-clients { padding: 60px 24px; }
  }


  /* ── TESTIMONIALS ── */
  .bio-testimonials {
    padding: 100px 48px;
    background: var(--chocolate);
  }

  .bio-testimonials-inner {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .bio-testimonials-track {
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

  .bio-testimonial-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 48px 40px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(184, 146, 42, 0.15);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(26, 18, 11, 0.4);
  }

  .bio-testimonial-text {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 24px);
    color: var(--cream);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .bio-testimonial-author {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--gold);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .bio-testimonials { padding: 80px 24px; }
    .bio-testimonial-card { padding: 32px 24px; }
  }
</style>
